The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the TSP with neighborhoods in the plane, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The authors use techniques such as linear programming and dynamic programming, which are commonly used in optimization problems and fall under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.SI).
